                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1831/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sack</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-29T15:00:00-06:00"
                            >September 29, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. Department’s telegram No. 58, September 28, 6 p.m., to Managua.<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d72fn11">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_520">p. 520</ref>.</note>
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs assures me that legislative <pb facs="0158" n="92"
                        xml:id="pg_92"/> approval of proposed trade agreement would be necessary.
                    Congress now meeting in extraordinary session of indefinite duration to which
                    President of Costa Rica could submit agreement by special message. Next regular
                    session convenes May 1st.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sack</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
